and contact us on #core-dev in Slack. -->
<!-- Provide an overview for maintainers and reviewers. -->
## Description

Move dynamic filter waiting logic from individual connectors into the engine layer.

**Motivation**

Quota from @raunaqmorarka 
> There's no reason why every connector should be hand rolling roughly similar waiting loop on DF. We did it this way in the beginning because connector was the only one benefitting from DFs in the past and it started from a small number of connectors. Since then the engine has gained dynamic row filtering and many more connectors have added similar waiting loop on DF.
The existing contract between engine and connectors for DFs is also overly complex because the io.trino.spi.connector.DynamicFilter API forces the connector to deal with an object that can update under the covers any time and reason about waiting on it. We want to eventually move io.trino.spi.connector.DynamicFilter out of SPI.

Move dynamic filter waiting logic from individual connectors into the engine layer by adding a TupleDomain<ColumnHandle> dynamicFilterPredicate parameter to ConnectorSplitSource#getNextBatch, so connectors receive the resolved predicate per batch without needing to hold a DynamicFilter and manage wait/timeout logic themselves.

Previously, Iceb

