## Description
Current test cases for orphan file removal are run as integration tests via the sql REMOVE_ORPHAN_FILES procedure. This PR adds standalone unittests that provide greater flexibility to test timestamp retention logic, and deletefiles (such as equality) that are unsupported by trino. All tests together execute very quickly in under a few seconds total.

## Additional context and related issues
Orphan file removal is a procedure which cleans up files from the backing storage (S3) that are no longer referenced by the iceberg metadata in order to save on storage costs. Files may become orphaned once we expire all the snapshots that reference them after a maintenance operation like compaction. Since orphan file removal is a destructive process (we're removing files from the storage) it's possible that it could potentially corrupt a table if not tested properly.

