PR DESCRIPTION:
## Description

Add support for reading and writing nanosecond precision timestamps (`TIMESTAMP(9)` and
`TIMESTAMP(9) WITH TIME ZONE`) in Iceberg v3 tables across all file formats (Parquet, ORC, Avro).

  File format support:
- Add Parquet reader decoder for INT64 NANOS to TIMESTAMP_TZ_NANOS
- Add Parquet writer for TIMESTAMP_TZ_NANOS
- Add ORC support for TIMESTAMP_NANO type in OrcTypeConverter
- Fix ORC file statistics to store nano timestamps in nanoseconds (was incorrectly using microseconds)
- Add Avro support for nanosecond timestamps (with and without timezone) in IcebergAvroDataConversion

Partition transforms:
  - Add support for year, month, day, and hour partition transforms on nano timestamp columns
  - Add getPreviousValue/getNextValue to LongTimestampType to enable partition constraint enforcement
  - Add nano timestamp handling to IcebergUtil.deserializePartitionValue()

  Expression handling:
  - Add bounds checking when converting Trino timestamps to Iceberg's 64-bit nanosecond representation
  - Update ExpressionConverter to return alwaysTrue()/alwaysFalse() for out-of-range predicates

## Release notes
(X) Release notes are required, with the following suggested text:

```markdown
## Iceberg
* Add support for reading and writing `timestamp(9)` and `timestamp(9) with time zone` in Iceberg v3 tables. ({issue}`issuenumber`)


